Self-doubt can be overwhelming, but at least recognize its omnipresence. Here are some tactics to help you step away from that spiral:

### 1. **Reframe Mistakes**: try viewing past mistakes differently, not as failures, but as lessons learned. Each mistake brings valuable insight into how to improve in the future, giving you an opportunity to do it differently and better next time.
*   &quot;I could have done this differently. The next time I'm in this situation, I will approach it by doing xyz instead of abc.&quot;
*   &quot;Although I faltered here, I successfully navigated similar situations before. Let me remember how I managed in those cases and apply that knowledge here.&quot;

